Context("Numeric");

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

# make this have the same root as the previous and following
SRAND($psvn);

$n = random(2,7,1);

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

Find the volume of the solid whose base is the region
in the first quadrant bounded by
\( y=x^{$n} \), \( y=1 \), and the \( y \)-axis
and whose cross-sections
perpendicular to the \(x\) axis are semicircles.

$PAR
Volume = \{ ans_rule(35) \}

END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS(num_cmp( "(1/8)*pi*(1 - 2/($n+1) + 1/(2*$n+1))" ) );

$twon = 2*$n;
$np1 = $n+1;
$c1 = ( $n/2 == int($n/2) ) ? "{2\over $np1}" : "{1\over " . ($np1/2) . "}";
$twonp1 = $twon + 1;

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR SOLUTION $PAR

Slicing perpendicularly to the \(x\) axis gives semicircles
whose thickness is \(\Delta x\) and whose diameter is \(1-y=1-x^{$n}\).
Thus
\[
\hbox{Volume of semicircular slice } \approx 
  {1\over 2} \pi \left(\frac{1-x^{$n}}2\right)^2\Delta x = 
  {1\over 8} \pi (1 - 2 x^{$n} + x^{$twon})\, \Delta x.
\]
Thus
\[
\hbox{Volume of solid } = 
  \int_0^1 {1\over 8}\pi (1 - 2 x^{$n} + x^{$twon})\, dx
\]
\[
  = {1\over 8}\pi(x - $c1 x^{$np1} + \frac{1}{$twonp1} x^{$twonp1})\Bigg|_0^1
\]
\[
  = {1\over 8}\pi(1 - $c1 + {1\over $twonp1}).
\]

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


